 a metropolitan residential population of over 375,000 but draw patients from a population base of more than one million people. Residency Programs Emergency Medicine Family Medicine Internal Medicine Internal Medicine – Transitional Internal Medicine-Pediatrics Neurology Neurosurgery Obstetrics & Gynecology Pediatrics Psychiatry Surgery Diagnostic Radiology Independent IR/DR Residency Fellowship Programs Breast Imaging Cardiovascular Diseases Gastroenterology Hospice & Palliative Medicine Neuroradiology Women’s Health Simulation Pulmonary Critical Care Emergency Medicine Ultrasound Contact Us Office of Graduate Medical Education One Illini Drive Peoria, Il 61605  Phone: 309-671-8450 Fax: 309-671-8452 Graduate Medical Education (GME) Residency Programs Fellowships Our Staff Resources Education About  Education  Research  Patient Care  Departments  News  Giving INFORMATION FOR: Prospective Students  Current Students  Faculty & Staff  Alumni & Friends  Patients RESOURCES: UIC Directory  Blackboard  Event Calendar  Emergency Information  Contact Us  Apply Now  Give  Contact Us Connect with us!      If you have questions, comments, or problems accessing this site, please E-mail the webmaster   Search for:    © Copyright 2020 University of Illinois College of Medicine   | Privacy Statement College of Medicine | Chicago | Peoria | Rockford | Urbana                                                                                                                                                  